The man burst into a hearty laugh. "They might be useful to me as relics of my adventure," said he,
"but beyond that I can hardly see what use the disjecta membra of my late acquaintance are going to
be to me. No, sir, I think that, with your permission, I will confine my attentions to the excellent
bird which I perceive upon the sideboard."

Sherlock Holmes glanced sharply across at me with a slight shrug of his shoulders.

"There is your hat, then, and there your bird," said he. "By the way, would it bore you to tell me
where you got the other one from? I am somewhat of a fowl fancier, and I have seldom seen a better
grown goose."